# api-endpoints

Core API Routes:

1. Meeting Management
Importance Score: 85/100
- POST /meetings/create
  - Extracts signals (decisions, actions, blockers) from meeting transcripts
  - Processes screenshots for visual context
  - Assigns meeting categories based on content analysis
  - Links related documents and participants

- PUT /meetings/{id}/signals  
  - Updates extracted signals with status transitions
  - Merges overlapping signals from different sources
  - Tracks signal approval workflow states
  - Links signals to sprint tasks and documents

2. Document Processing 
Importance Score: 80/100
- POST /documents/upload
  - Classifies document type and purpose
  - Extracts relevant signals and knowledge items
  - Maps document relationships in knowledge graph
  - Links to associated meetings and tickets

- PUT /documents/{id}/categorize
  - Updates document categorization
  - Processes document relationships
  - Extracts new signals from content updates
  - Maintains document version history

3. Signal Management
Importance Score: 90/100
- POST /signals/extract
  - Processes meeting/document content for signal extraction
  - Categorizes signals (decision, action, blocker, risk, idea)
  - Assigns signal priority and status
  - Links signals to knowledge graph entities

- PUT /signals/{id}/status
  - Updates signal workflow status
  - Handles signal approval/rejection flow
  - Tracks signal archival states
  - Maintains signal relationship mapping

4. Knowledge Integration
Importance Score: 75/100 
- POST /knowledge/map
  - Creates knowledge graph relationships
  - Maps signal connections and dependencies
  - Tracks knowledge entity progression
  - Links related meetings and documents

